race.comment: CAP CAVOUR (1) has jumped favourite in all 3 runs this time in, flying late to be 1.5L off the winner. The in-form Wheatley hops in the saddle now and the form out of his last start has worked out nicely. Can storm home over the top and return to winning ways. FOUR SEAS (5) sat handy last start over this trip at Mt Barker last time out. She'll be fitter again now as she comes here third-up and her only victory has come when third-up. Should get every chance in the run and is sure to go close. BUSTER'S GIRL (2) can take up the running from barrier one after tiring late over 1200m last time out. Her two runs prior at this trip were solid and she can be in this for a long way with the 4kg claim on board. MARYBEE (6) is better than she showed last start and can bounce back. FAVAIOS (3) is worth including on his last start effort.
